cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL

The paper proposes a new technique for improving the optimization efficiency and generalization ability of Batch Normalization (BN) in deep neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) since the experiments involve convolutional neural networks. The paper also discusses the impact of the proposed technique on the optimization process, which suggests relevance to sub-categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing experiments, which could suggest relevance to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
